\subsection{Sisterhood}

This chant is of course inspired by the famous soap maker, Dr. Bronner who's "All-in-one" soap was produced specifically as a distribution mechanism for the scripture on the bottles. When we first recorded the chant for the Naad Your Heart album, Emilio started doing the following series of gestures, or mudrās.
\index{mudra}
According to Wikipedia: A \textbf{mudra} (/mu'drɑ:/; Sanskrit mudrā, ``seal", ``mark", or ``gesture"; Tibetan: \texttibetan{ཕྱག་རྒྱ་} THL chakgya) is a symbolic or ritual gesture in Hinduism and Buddhism. Some mudras involve the entire body; most are performed with just hands and fingers. A mudrā is a spiritual gesture and an energetic seal of authenticity employed in the iconography and spiritual practice of Indian religions.

One hundred and eight mudras are used in regular Tantric rituals.

